<title>GERMANY: Daimler says Q1 sales up 12 percent.</title>
<headline>Daimler says Q1 sales up 12 percent.</headline>
<dateline>STUTTGART, Germany 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months to March 31, 1997</p>
<p>(in millions of marks unless stated)</p>
<p>    Group sales				  25,906  vs 23,444</p>
<p>Of which:</p>
<p>    --European Union			   14,976  vs 14,456</p>
<p>    --Germany				    8,420   vs 8,635</p>
<p>    --EU excluding Germany		   6,556   vs 5,821</p>
<p>    --United States			    5,228   vs 4,265</p>
<p>    --Other markets			    5,702   vs 4,723</p>
<p>    Group workforce			    287,636 vs 292,478</p>
<p>Of which:</p>
<p>    --Germany				    220,032 vs 225,525</p>
<p>    --Foreign				    67,604  vs 66,953</p>
<p>    Passenger car revenues		   11,426  vs 10,313</p>
<p>Passenger vehicle production (units)     161,696 vs 163,326</p>
<p>    Passenger car sales (units)	    154,011 vs 147,994</p>
<p>    Passenger division workforce	   85,492  vs 82,508</p>
<p>    Commercial vehicle revenues	    8,157   vs 7,438</p>
<p>Commercial vehicle production (units)    93,100  vs 88,499</p>
<p>    Commercial vehicle sales (units)     84,927  vs 80,841</p>
<p>    Commercial vehicle workforce	   80,732  vs 79,852</p>
<p>    Aerospace revenues			 2,827   vs 2,325</p>
<p>    Aerospace incoming orders		2,587   vs 5,641</p>
<p>    Aerospace employees			44,076  vs 49,172</p>
<p>    Debis services revenues		  3,305   vs 2,960</p>
<p>    Debis services workforce		 12,111  vs 10,327</p>
<p>    Rail systems revenues		    605     vs 554</p>
<p>    Rail systems incoming orders	   1,032   vs 821</p>
<p>    Rail systems workforce		   10,865  vs 11,347</p>
<p>    Microelectronics revenues		541     vs 627</p>
<p>    Microelectronics incoming orders     661     vs 602</p>
<p>    Microelectronics workforce	     10,790  vs 11,794</p>
<p>    MTU/Diesel engines revenues	    322     vs 306</p>
<p>    MTU/Diesel engines incoming orderes  408     vs 407</p>
<p>    MTU/Diesel workforce		     5,580   vs 5,606</p>
<p>NOTE - Full name of the German industrial group is Daimler-Benz AG. Daimler said its sales, adjusted for changes in the group, rose by about 12 percent. All of the groups contributed to the business expansion, including its directly-managed businesses.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
